1. Purge Binary Logs via MySQL

-- Purge logs older than 3 days
PURGE BINARY LOGS BEFORE NOW() - INTERVAL 3 DAY;

-- OR purge everything except the latest log
PURGE BINARY LOGS TO 'binlog.001154';


1. Update the Configuration
In your MySQL configuration file (likely /etc/mysql/mysql.conf.d/mysqld.cnf), update the setting:

[mysqld]
binlog_expire_logs_seconds = 604800

2. Apply the Change Immediately
You can apply this to the running server without a restart by logging into the MySQL shell:

SQL
SET GLOBAL binlog_expire_logs_seconds = 604800;

3. Cleanup Existing Logs
The setting above only affects future logs or triggers when a new log is created.

SQL
PURGE BINARY LOGS BEFORE NOW() - INTERVAL 7 DAY;
